/*
 * Used only by `npm run test:mutation` (Stryker). Stryker instruments source files by wrapping
 * mutated expressions in runtime `condition ? mutant : original` switches; when a mutation
 * narrows/widens the inferred type of a value that flows into a template binding (e.g. removing
 * a `?? []` fallback), Angular's strict template type-checker rejects the resulting union type as
 * a compile error before Stryker ever gets to run a single test. Turning off strictTemplates here
 * (regular `npm test`/builds are unaffected - they use tsconfig.spec.json/tsconfig.app.json)
 * relaxes that check so mutated code still compiles; the mutants are still exercised by the real
 * test assertions exactly as before.
 */
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.spec.json",
  "angularCompilerOptions": {
    "strictTemplates": false
  }
}
